node.text: Learning one of my last fight sequences. Maybe my favorite Maze fight ever. Shot in one shot. Thank you @vladrimburg for your vision, your creativity and for trusting me. You have been so instrumental to Mazikeen’s grit and fight. Can’t wait for @lucifernetflix fans to see it. 😈

node.text: Such a wonderful conversation for an important cause. Join me and Paolo in starting your fitness and well-being journey while helping bring safe and respectful birth to mothers across the US and globally. @paolomascitti and I are Team Maze for Moms! The hardest step is the first one and we are here to help. Thank you @cturlington and @everymomcounts Love and light, Lesley-Ann and Paolo xxx Link in my Bio

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lesley-Ann Brandt on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: I once sat across another mother at lunch who proceeded to tell me I shouldn’t get my son vaccinated. I was pregnant at the time. Note to well intending mothers, don’t do that. I listened to all the reasons she had, none of which made any sense to me. I’d taken a vaccination class with my husband so that we understood how things worked in the US and for me, how different it was to both South Africa and New Zealand. Together with our pediatrician, we decided to space his  vaccines out a little further. What this mother didn’t take into consideration, was that she was sitting opposite someone who was born on a continent where virus’s had ravaged parts of it. (No where near the death toll of Covid 19 worldwide). A continent where people come to shoot our wildlife and do their safaris and have no problem getting vaccines in order to have THAT experience. Vaccination passports already exist in order to do those things. I was never not going to vaccinate my son. I was going to be informed.  As should we all but the absolute inaccuracies and misinformation going around is truly insane. Children are now dying. Getting really sick. The ICU’s are filling up again. The countless stories of unvaccinated sending their last message out to the world, “I thought I knew better, I should have got the vaccine”. Didn’t have to be that way. A father of 5 didn’t have to die. And yes, vaccinated people can still get it, but they are not the ones being intubated right now. They are not the ones in ICU, dying. The numbers of unvaccinated to vaccinated currently in hospital is staggering. So my question to those unwilling, not those TRULY unable, if you don’t believe in the science and medicine to prevent your death or the very real long term effects of this virus, why when you contract it, do you go to a hospital or doctor to help you when you do? Be safe. Get vaccinated. Please, continue to wear a mask. LAB x

node.text: Been told I look like her most of my adult life and at least once a week from a stranger. A huge compliment to be honest. The fact that she turns 55 today, directed her first movie,  Bruised, where she portrays an MMA fighter shattering this age old idea in Hollywood that women over 40 are done. She’s not the first  but it’s damn good to see her physically strong and doing it. Always been on list of actresses who inspire me to keep going. To create the roles you want and to use the every No as motivation. Happy birthday director @halleberry I can’t wait to see Bruised.

node.text: Spent the most incredible day with @peta and @lionstigers_andbears . This sanctuary offers a safe haven for bears, lions and tigers who have been rescued or discarded by exploitive breeders in the the cub petting industry. Babies who are ripped from their mothers almost immediately after birth. Today Kingston learned that while it is wonderful to have sanctuaries like this one who are committed the animal’s wellbeing, they really should be in the wild and not used for human entertainment. Photo ops with, rides on, petting of ANY wild animal is abuse. Thank you for your incredible work Bobbi. Please support @lionstigers_andbears LAB x
